      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/28/4",
      "text": [
        " الرَّجُلِ يَكُونُ لَهُ عَلَى الرَّجُلِ الْمَالُ فَإِذَا حَلَّ قَالَ لَهُ بِعْنِي مَتَاعاً حَتَّى أَبِيعَهُ وَ أَقْضِيَكَ الَّذِي لَكَ عَلَيَّ قَالَ لَا بَأْسَ بِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4035 - It is narrated from Bakkar ibn Abi Bakr, from Abu Abdullah (as), regarding a man who has a debt owed to him by another man. When the debt becomes due, the debtor says to him, \"Sell me some goods so that I may sell them and repay you what I owe.\"\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
